column3: Automatic sanity-testing: PASSED, see http://jenkins.bluematt.me/pull-tester/b26f9d893cb3b8b5ff74e7c71217181def1c2783 for binaries and test log.\nThis test script verifies pulls every time they are updated. It, however, dies sometimes and fails to test properly.  If you are waiting on a test, please check timestamps to verify that the test.log is moving at http://jenkins.bluematt.me/pull-tester/cu
Is the (QMainWindow*) needed here? I'd think it would do upcasting automatically.\n
For messages, which are received from outside BitcoinGUI, it was not working as it should.\n
Yes, I agree that this extra parameter is a good idea. But I specifically mean that cast, won't just `, this` work just as well?\n
Indeed just `this` does the job and I updated the pull.\n
